The to-be-printed version of page (?decorator=printable) should do a better job of providing access back to the page itself and to links referenced in the printout.  This could be improved in two ways:

Include the URL for the printed page at the top of the printed page.  The browser doesn't always include that in the page header, and if it's long it may be truncated.

Links inside the printed version should be expanded in this view.  It's hard for me to double click or mouse over an underlined phrase when it's on paper.  It should include the underlined linked phrase, and in parenthesis or brackets behind it, the full URL of the link.

